<p>
<seg id=1> Ground controllers of the nonstop worldwide Hot-air balloon flight said that three riders on the balloon should leave the Chinese airspace and fly eastward across the Pacific Ocean. </seg>
<seg id=2> The three riders met with political troubles on Tuesday when the balloon drifted off the corridor set by the Chinese government. </seg>
<seg id=3> Chinese officials once ordered them to land on China's Tibet, which was canceled through negotiations by British and American diplomats. </seg>
